# Testing and Quality Gates

- Every meaningful change must include unit tests, integration tests, and load/performance coverage.
- If one test layer cannot be added immediately, require explicit justification plus a tracked TODO.
- Add regression tests for bugs before/with the fix.
- For UI changes, test critical flows and visual/layout invariants (especially Castle centering and safe areas).
- For backend/model changes, include failure-mode and edge-case coverage.
- Do not consider work complete unless tests pass for affected behavior.
- Prefer deterministic tests and stable fixtures over brittle timing-dependent tests.